Project Report
Intelligent Book Recommendation System using Text Mining and Machine Learning
Abstract

The rapid growth of online bookstores and digital libraries has made it increasingly difficult for users to discover books matching their interests. Traditional keyword-based search systems often fail to capture semantic relationships between books. This project develops a Content-Based Book Recommendation System using Text Mining and Machine Learning techniques. The system preprocesses textual information, extracts numerical features using TF-IDF, computes cosine similarity, and recommends similar books through an interactive interface. The project demonstrates the complete machine learning pipeline including data preprocessing, feature extraction, recommendation generation, evaluation, and visualization.

Chapter 1
Introduction

Recommendation systems are widely used in e-commerce, streaming platforms, and digital libraries to improve user experience. A Content-Based Recommendation System recommends items based on their textual characteristics rather than user ratings.

This project recommends books using:

Book Description
Genres
Author
Publisher

The recommendations are generated using TF-IDF Vectorization and Cosine Similarity.

Chapter 2
Problem Statement

Users often struggle to discover books that match their interests because of the vast amount of available content.

The objective is to build an intelligent recommendation engine capable of identifying semantically similar books based on textual information.

Chapter 3
Objectives
Load a book dataset
Perform data cleaning
Conduct Exploratory Data Analysis
Preprocess textual data
Generate TF-IDF vectors
Compute cosine similarity
Recommend Top-N similar books
Build an interactive interface

