Output

Harry Potter and the Chamber of Secrets
Harry Potter and the Prisoner of Azkaban
Fantastic Beasts and Where to Find Them
Percy Jackson and the Lightning Thief
Chapter 9
Evaluation

Evaluation Metrics

Cosine Similarity Score
Recommendation Quality
Semantic Similarity

Advantages

Simple
Fast
Interpretable

Limitations

Cannot recommend unseen preferences
Does not use user ratings
Chapter 10
Conclusion

The Intelligent Book Recommendation System successfully demonstrates the application of Text Mining and Machine Learning in personalized recommendation systems. The use of TF-IDF and Cosine Similarity enables effective content-based recommendations while providing an interactive interface suitable for practical use.

